\is1 Introduction
\ip This account about Yehoshua, traditionally âJoshuaâ in English (after âIâ and then âJâ changed over the centuries from a âYâ sound), tells how the Israelis invaded Canaan and took control of the land. Yehoshua led them forward now after replacing Mosheh (Moses) when he passed away somewhere on a mountain. Some of the main events described in this document include: their crossing the Yordan river, the demolition of Yericho (traditionally âJerichoâ), the war at Ay, the allocation of blocks of land to the various Israeli tribes and others, and the renewal of the agreement between God and his people.
\ip The most well-known saying in this account is, ââŠchoose for yourselves today who you will serveâŠ But as for me and my household, we will serve Yahweh.â (24:15).
\iot Main components of this account
\io1 The defeat of the Canaanites \ior 1:1â12:24\ior*
\io1 The division of land \ior 13:1â21:45\ior*
\io2 a. The land east of the River Yordan \ior 13:1-33\ior*
\io2 b. The land west of the River Yordan \ior 14:1â19:51\ior*
\io2 c. The refuge cities \ior 20:1-9\ior*
\io2 d. The cities for Levites \ior 21:1-45\ior*
\io1 The returning home of some tribes back to the east of the Yordan \ior 22:1-34\ior*
\io1 Yehoshua's final instructions \ior 23:1-16\ior*
\io1 The renewal of the agreement there at Shikim \ior 24:1-33\ior*
