\v 1 Then YahwehÂŠ102328 told Yehoshua, âDon'tÂŠ102332 \add âbe afraid or discouragedÂŠ102337\add*. Take all your warriors withÂŠ102351 you and go to Ay. Listen, I'veÂŠ102350 givenÂŠ102350 \add âyou victory over\add* Ay's kingÂŠ102354 and his people and his cityÂŠ102361 and his landÂŠ102364.
\v 2 You'll doÂŠ102366 to Ay and its king what you did to Yericho and its king,\f + \fr 8:2 \ft We're not actually given any details about what happened to the king of Yericho.\f* except that you all can plunder its spoil and its livestock for yourselvesÂŠ102381. Ambush the city from behind.â
\p
\v 3 \add âSoÂŠ102386\add* Yehoshua \add âled\add* his warriors towards Ay. \add *He\add* choseÂŠ102394 thirtyÂŠ102396 thousandÂŠ102397 of the \add âbravest and strongest warriors\add* and sentÂŠ102401 them \add âahead in the darkness\add*
\v 4 and toldÂŠ102404 them, âListenÂŠ102405, you all lie in ambush againstÂŠ102410 the city from close behindÂŠ102411 \add *it\add*, and \add âmake sure you all stay alert and ready\add* \add to attack\add*.
\v 5 \add âI will bring those warriors\add* who are withÂŠ102440 me andÂŠ102424 we'll approach the cityÂŠ102433, thenÂŠ102424 when theyÂŠ102437 comeÂŠ102437 out to \add âattack\add* us like \add âlast time\add*, we'll run back away from them.
\v 6 They'llÂŠ102448 \add âthink we're running away from them like we did before, so they'll chase afterÂŠ102445 us untilÂŠ102446 we've drawnÂŠ102447 them away\add* from the cityÂŠ102451.
\v 7 ThenÂŠ102461 you'll all \add âmove inÂŠ102471\add* from your ambushÂŠ102463 \add position\add* and capture the city, and your godÂŠ102470 YahwehÂŠ102469 \add âwill give the city to you all\add*.
\v 8 \add âAfter\add* you captureÂŠ102474 the city, set fire to it. Do what I'veÂŠ102487 orderedÂŠ102487 you all \add âwhich inÂŠ102482 turn has come from\add* YahwehÂŠ102484.
\v 9 \add âSoÂŠ102490\add* Yehoshua sentÂŠ102490 them to \add set up\add* the ambushÂŠ102495 between Ay andÂŠ102490 Beyt-El (so west of Ay). \add âMeanwhile,\add* \add *he\add* stayed overnight \add âatÂŠ102507 the camp\add*.
\p
\v 10 Yehoshua got up earlyÂŠ102512 in the morningÂŠ102514 and gathered the \add âwarriors\add*, thenÂŠ102512 he and the IsraeliÂŠ102521 eldersÂŠ102521 went \add âin frontÂŠ102523 of them\add* \add to go and attack\add* Ay.
\v 11 \add *They all\add* wentÂŠ102533 close to the cityÂŠ102537 and campedÂŠ102538 \add there slightly\add* to the northÂŠ102539, with just a valley betweenÂŠ102544 them and AyÂŠ102540.
\v 12 (He had sent around fiveÂŠ102549 thousandÂŠ102550 warriors to \add âlie in\add* ambushÂŠ102554 between Beyt-El andÂŠ102548 Ay, west of the cityÂŠ102562,
\v 13 \add âso\add* the main group was to the northÂŠ102572 andÂŠ102564 the rear guardÂŠ102576 to the west.) That nightÂŠ102581 Yehoshua wentÂŠ102579 down into the valleyÂŠ102584.
\v 14 WhenÂŠ102586 the king of Ay saw \add <the IsraelisÂŠ102604\add*, he hurriedlyÂŠ102591 got his men ready, and went out earlyÂŠ102592 to meet YisraelÂŠ102599 for the battleÂŠ102600. The king and his peopleÂŠ102604 went to a \add âprepared spot overlooking the Yordan valley, butÂŠ102586\add* he didn'tÂŠ102609 know that \add âanother group lay in ambushÂŠ102613 behindÂŠ102615 the city\add*.
\v 15 Yehoshua andÂŠ102618 the Israeli group allowed themselves to be struckÂŠ102618 by them, thenÂŠ102618 they fledÂŠ102624 back towards the wildernessÂŠ102626
\v 16 and all the \add âmen\add* inÂŠ102633 the city were calledÂŠ102628 out to chase them. \add âSoÂŠ102628\add* they chased after YehoshuaÂŠ102639 and were drawnÂŠ102640 away from the city,
\v 17 and there wasn't a single man left inÂŠ102649 Ay or Beyt-El who didn'tÂŠ102645 \add âjoin the chase\add*âtheyÂŠ102655 left the cityÂŠ102661 \add wide\add* openÂŠ102662 and chased after the Israelis.
\p
\v 18 Then YahwehÂŠ102669 told Yehoshua, âHold your spear out \add âpointing\add* towards Ay, becauseÂŠ102681 I will \add âallow you to defeat it\add*.â \add âSo\add* Yehoshua held the spear thatÂŠ102675 was inÂŠ102674 his hand out toward the cityÂŠ102692.
\v 19 \add âWhenÂŠ102706 the warriors inÂŠ102709 the ambushÂŠ102694 saw that, they\add* rushed out from theirÂŠ102697 placeÂŠ102697 and entered the city and capturedÂŠ102703 it, and quicklyÂŠ102696 set \add *it\add* onÂŠ102709 fire.
\v 20 \add WhenÂŠ102711\add* the men from AyÂŠ102713 turned andÂŠ102711 lookedÂŠ102711 behindÂŠ102714 them, the smokeÂŠ102718 from their cityÂŠ102719 was going up into the sky, \add âbutÂŠ102711 they had nowhere to escape to.\add* ThenÂŠ102711 \add @Yehoshua's men\add* who'd been fleeingÂŠ102730 towards the wildernessÂŠ102731 turned back around towards their pursuersÂŠ102735
\v 21 and saw that the ambushÂŠ102745 had capturedÂŠ102744 the city and the smokeÂŠ102751 was rising. \add âSoÂŠ102737\add* they \add âcontinued back towards AyÂŠ102740, killing their men\add*.
\v 22 \add âMeanwhile,\add* \add @their warriors\add* cameÂŠ102761 \add back\add* out of the cityÂŠ102764, \add âso\add* the men from Ay ended up inÂŠ102768 the middleÂŠ102768 of the two groups, andÂŠ102760 \add @the Israelis\add* \add âfought untilÂŠ102775 they'd killed them all\add*.
\v 23 \add âHowever\add* theyÂŠ102788 capturedÂŠ102788 the kingÂŠ102786 of Ay aliveÂŠ102789 andÂŠ102790 broughtÂŠ102790 him to Yehoshua.
\p
\v 24 ThenÂŠ102796 \add âafter the IsraelisÂŠ102820\add* had finishedÂŠ102797 killingÂŠ102799 the \add âmen of\add* Ay who had chased them \add towards\add* the wildernessÂŠ102807, \add *they\add* returnedÂŠ102819 to Ay andÂŠ102796 \add âslaughtered the people still inÂŠ102807 there\add*,
\v 25 \add âso a totalÂŠ102831 of\add* twelve thousandÂŠ102842 men andÂŠ102830 women from AyÂŠ102845 \add âwere killed\add* that dayÂŠ102834.
\v 26 Yehoshua didn'tÂŠ102848 \add âlower his\add* spear untilÂŠ102855 everyone who lived inÂŠ102854 Ay had been completely destroyedÂŠ102857.
\v 27 \add âThe Israelis\add* only took the livestock andÂŠ102866 the goods from \add âAy\add*, just as YahwehÂŠ102873 had instructedÂŠ102875 Yehoshua,
\v 28 thenÂŠ102880 YehoshuaÂŠ102881 burntÂŠ102880 the city andÂŠ102885 madeÂŠ102885 itÂŠ102885 a \add âpermanentÂŠ102888 pile of rubble where no one lives to this dayÂŠ102891\add*.
\v 29 \add *He\add* hangedÂŠ102898 the kingÂŠ102896 of Ay on a tree, \add âbutÂŠ102894\add* as the sunÂŠ102907 was going down, \add *he\add* commandedÂŠ102908 that the corpseÂŠ102913 be brought down from the tree. They threwÂŠ102917 it into the cityÂŠ102923 gateway andÂŠ102894 piled a big heap of rocksÂŠ102928 on top of it which is still there today.
\s1 The reading of Law there at Mt. Eybal
\rem /s1 Joshua Renews the Covenant; The Lord's Covenant Renewed; The Law Is Read at Mount Ebal; The Covenant Renewed at Mount Ebal
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 30 Then Yehoshua builtÂŠ102936 an altarÂŠ102938 to Yisrael'sÂŠ102941 godÂŠ102940, YahwehÂŠ102939 onÂŠ102942 MtÂŠ102942. Eybal\x + \xo 8:30-32: \xt Deu 27:2-8.\x*
\v 31 just like Yahweh'sÂŠ102950 servantÂŠ102948 Mosheh had instructedÂŠ102946 \add *them\add*. (It was writtenÂŠ102955 inÂŠ102956 the scroll of the rules from Mosheh \add that it must be\add* an altarÂŠ102959 made from whole stonesÂŠ102960 that \add âhaven't been chiselled withÂŠ102956\add* iron tools.) Then they offered burntÂŠ102970 offerings to Yahweh onÂŠ102956 it, plusÂŠ102968 they sacrificedÂŠ102972 peaceÂŠ102973 offerings,\x + \xo 8:31: \xt Exo 20:25.\x*
\v 32 andÂŠ102975 \add âwhile the IsraelisÂŠ102989 watched,\add* \add @Yehoshua\add* inscribed onto the stones \add thereÂŠ102977\add*,\f + \fr 8:32 \ft Probably not the altar stones since an iron tool wasn't allowed to be used on them.\f* a copy of the rules \add âpassed on by\add* MoshehÂŠ102984.
\v 33 ThenÂŠ102991 all of YisraelÂŠ102993 and theirÂŠ103015 eldersÂŠ102994 and officialsÂŠ102995 and judgesÂŠ102997 were standingÂŠ102998 \add âsome on each side\add* of the box containing Yahweh's agreementÂŠ103010, \add âfacing\add* the priestsÂŠ103005 and the LevitesÂŠ103006 who carriedÂŠ103007 the box. Any resident foreigners were also there. Half of the people stood on the Mt. Gerazim side, and half on the Mt. Eybal side \add of the valley\add*, just like \add the way that\add* Yahweh's servantÂŠ103032 MoshehÂŠ103031 had originally commandedÂŠ103030 for blessingÂŠ103035 the people.\x + \xo 8:33-35: \xt Deu 11:29; 27:11-14.\x*
\p
\v 34 ThenÂŠ103042 YehoshuaÂŠ103046 read all the law, \add includingÂŠ103053\add* the blessingsÂŠ103052 andÂŠ103053 the cursesÂŠ103053, as per everythingÂŠ103054 that's writtenÂŠ103056 inÂŠ103057 the book of the law.
\v 35 \add *He\add* \add âread out every single word thatÂŠ103069 MoshehÂŠ103068 had written\add*, inÂŠ103083 front of the entireÂŠ103064 assemblyÂŠ103077 of YisraelÂŠ103078, includingÂŠ103079 the womenÂŠ103079, children, and foreigners living amongÂŠ103083 them.
\c 9
\s1 The Gibeonites deceive Yehoshua
\rem /s1 The Gibeonites Save Themselves by Trickery; The Gibeonite Deception; The Gibeonites Deceive Israel; The Gibeonites Deceive Joshua
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 1 \add âThere were several kingsÂŠ103090 who ruled in regions onÂŠ103092 this west sideÂŠ103092 of the YordanÂŠ103093âthe HittitesÂŠ103104 and AmoritesÂŠ103105, the CanaanitesÂŠ103106 and PerizzitesÂŠ103107, the HivitesÂŠ103108 and the Yebusites. Some were in the hill countryÂŠ103094, some in the lowlandsÂŠ103095, and some along the Mediterranean coastÂŠ103097 south of LebanonÂŠ103103\add*. \add When\add* \add *they\add* heardÂŠ103087 about \add @what had happened atÂŠ103092 Ay\add*,
\v 2 theyÂŠ103111 \add âformed an alliance\add* to fightÂŠ103113 \add togetherÂŠ103112\add* against YehoshuaÂŠ103116 andÂŠ103117 YisraelÂŠ103119.
\p
\v 3 \add âHowever,\add* when \add the people who\add* live in GibeonÂŠ103125 heardÂŠ103126 what Yehoshua had doneÂŠ103129 to YerichoÂŠ103131 and Ay,
\v 4 they \add âdecided to use cunningÂŠ103138\add* \add instead\add*. They \add âfound old, worn-out sacksÂŠ103142 to throw over theirÂŠ103144 donkeysÂŠ103144 and old, worn-out wineskins that had been torn and mendedÂŠ103149, thenÂŠ103134 sent men to act as ambassadorsÂŠ103140\add*.
\v 5 \add âThey found worn-out sandalsÂŠ103151 that had been patchedÂŠ103153, and wore worn-out clothesÂŠ103155.\add* All the \add âfoodÂŠ103159 that they took for the journey was already dry and disintegrating into crumbsÂŠ103163\add*.
\v 6 They wentÂŠ103165 to Yehoshua in the campÂŠ103171 at GilgalÂŠ103172 and told him, âWe've comeÂŠ103181 from a far-off landÂŠ103179 and \add âwant you to makeÂŠ103183 a treaty with\add* us.â
\p
\v 7 An IsraeliÂŠ103190 manÂŠ103190 asked the Hivite \add (because Gilead was inÂŠ103197 the Hivite region)\add*, âPerhaps you really live near by? How could we makeÂŠ103201 a treaty withÂŠ103197 you?â\x + \xo 9:7: \xt Exo 23:32; 34:12; Deu 7:2.\x*
\p
\v 8 They \add âaddressed\add* Yehoshua, âWe are yourÂŠ103211 servantsÂŠ103211.â
\p Yehoshua \add âasked\add* them, âWho are you? And whereÂŠ103218 have you comeÂŠ103219 from?â
\p
\v 9 âYour servantsÂŠ103227 have comeÂŠ103226 from a very distantÂŠ103224 landÂŠ103223,â they replied, âbecauseÂŠ103228 of the reputationÂŠ103228 of your godÂŠ103230, YahwehÂŠ103229. We've heardÂŠ103233 the \add #reports\add* about himÂŠ103234 andÂŠ103221 everything that heÂŠ103239 didÂŠ103239 inÂŠ103240 EgyptÂŠ103240,
\v 10 and everything that he didÂŠ103247 to the twoÂŠ103248 AmoriteÂŠ103250 kingsÂŠ103249 onÂŠ103252 the otherÂŠ103252 sideÂŠ103252 of the YordanÂŠ103253âKing SihonÂŠ103254 of HeshbonÂŠ103256, and King OgÂŠ103257 of the BashanÂŠ103260 who \add âlived\add* inÂŠ103252 AshtarothÂŠ103262.\x + \xo 9:10: \xt Num 21:21-35.\x*
\v 11 \add âSoÂŠ103264\add* our eldersÂŠ103266 and all those who live inÂŠ103273 our area instructed us, âTake provisionsÂŠ103274 for the \add âjourneyÂŠ103275\add* and goÂŠ103276 to meet them, and tell them, âWe are yourÂŠ103273 servantsÂŠ103280. \add âNow makeÂŠ103283 a treaty withÂŠ103273\add* us.â â
\v 12 ThisÂŠ103293 breadÂŠ103290 of ours was warm \add âfrom our ovens\add* when we loaded it \add âfor our journey\add*, and now, look, it's \add all\add* dry and crumblingÂŠ103303.
\v 13 And these wineskins were new when weÂŠ103309 filledÂŠ103309 them, and look, \add now\add* they're \add all\add* torn. \add âSame with\add* our clothesÂŠ103314 and our sandalsÂŠ103315âthey're \add all\add* worn-out from the very \add âlongÂŠ103317 journeyÂŠ103318\add*.â
\p
\v 14 The \add âIsraeli leaders tasted\add* some of theirÂŠ103323 provisionsÂŠ103323, butÂŠ103321 they didn'tÂŠ103328 ask YahwehÂŠ103327 \add âfor advice\add*.
\v 15 \add âSoÂŠ103331\add* Yehoshua \add âagreed to\add* make peaceÂŠ103334 with them, and theyÂŠ103339 made a treaty \add ânot to attack their people\add*, and all the Israeli leadersÂŠ103341 promised that.
\p
\v 16 \add âHowever, threeÂŠ103346 daysÂŠ103347 afterÂŠ103348 making the treaty, they discovered that those people actually lived quite close to where they were\add*.
\v 17 ThenÂŠ103364 the IsraelisÂŠ103367 wentÂŠ103368 on forward and they arrived at those cities on the thirdÂŠ103373 dayâthe cities of GibeonÂŠ103375, KefirahÂŠ103376, BeerotÂŠ103377, and Kiryat-Yearim.
\v 18 ButÂŠ103381 \add *they\add* didn'tÂŠ103381 \add âattackÂŠ103382 those cities\add* becauseÂŠ103385 \add *their\add* leaders had made a promise by the godÂŠ103392 of YisraelÂŠ103384, YahwehÂŠ103391.
\p \add âAllÂŠ103393 the IsraelisÂŠ103384\add* grumbledÂŠ103394 against their leaders for making that treaty,
\v 19 \add âbutÂŠ103402\add* their leadersÂŠ103405 told \add *them\add*, âWeÂŠ103416 ourselves have promisedÂŠ103412 them by \add *our\add* GodÂŠ103415 YahwehÂŠ103414 \add âso\add* now we can'tÂŠ103418 touchÂŠ103420 them.
\v 20 We're \add âforced now to let them liveÂŠ103426, otherwise God's angerÂŠ103432 would be against us for breaking our promise\add* to them.
\v 21 \add âSoÂŠ103441\add* we'll let them liveÂŠ103444 \add butÂŠ103441 make them our slaves\add*.â \add âAs a result of that,\add* \add @the Gibeonites\add* became woodcutters andÂŠ103441 water-carriersÂŠ103450 for all the \add âIsraelis\add*.
\p
\v 22 ThenÂŠ103459 Yehoshua summoned them andÂŠ103459 asked them, âWhy didÂŠ103466 you all deceiveÂŠ103466 us \add âby telling us that you lived far away when really you were very close\add*?
\v 23 \add âBecause of that,\add* you're all cursedÂŠ103478 and you'll always be our slavesÂŠ103484âyou'll all be the woodcutters and water-carriersÂŠ103489 for the houseÂŠ103490 of my godÂŠ103491.â
\p
\v 24 âBecause it was \add âmade very clear\add* to your servantsÂŠ103501,â they answeredÂŠ103493, âthat your godÂŠ103506 YahwehÂŠ103505 had commandedÂŠ103504 his servantÂŠ103510 MoshehÂŠ103509 to giveÂŠ103511 to you all the land andÂŠ103493 to destroyÂŠ103518 everyone who lives in the region. \add âWe fearedÂŠ103526 for our lives when you came closer\add*, so that's what we didÂŠ103530.
\v 25 \add âSoÂŠ103536 now we're inÂŠ103538 your powerâdoÂŠ103544 to us whatever you think\add* is goodÂŠ103539 andÂŠ103536 rightÂŠ103540.â
\v 26 \add âSoÂŠ103546\add* that's what \add @Yehoshua\add* did andÂŠ103546 he \add âprevented the IsraelisÂŠ103554\add* from killing them.
\v 27 \add âInsteadÂŠ103559\add* \add *he\add* made them \add âmove to where he wanted, to become\add* woodcutters and water-carriersÂŠ103565 for the people and for Yahweh'sÂŠ103568 altarÂŠ103567 untilÂŠ103569 this day.
\c 10
\s1 The defeat of the Amorites
\rem /s1 The Amorites Are Defeated; The Sun Stands Still; The conquest of the south; Israel Defeats the Southern Kings
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 1 \add âOnce\add* KingÂŠ103585 AdoniÂŠ103582-TsedekÂŠ103584 of YerushalemÂŠ103586 heard that Yehoshua had capturedÂŠ103589 Ay and completely destroyedÂŠ103594 it, and that he'd treated the king of Ay the same as he had treated the king of YerichoÂŠ103597, and he heard that the Gibeonites had made peace withÂŠ103612 YisraelÂŠ103610 and were \add now working for\add* them,
\v 2 \add @the people of Yerushalem\add* were very afraidÂŠ103614 becauseÂŠ103623 GibeonÂŠ103619 had been a powerful cityÂŠ103617, stronger than Ay, andÂŠ103614 all it's warriorsÂŠ103632 were powerful.
\v 3 \add âSoÂŠ103634\add* King AdoniÂŠ103635-TsedekÂŠ103637 sentÂŠ103634 to King HohamÂŠ103642 of HebronÂŠ103645, King PiramÂŠ103648 of Yarmut, King YafiaÂŠ103654 of Lakish, andÂŠ103634 King DebirÂŠ103660 of EglonÂŠ103663, saying,
\v 4 âCome \add âhere\add* and helpÂŠ103669 me. We'll attackÂŠ103670 GibeonÂŠ103673 becauseÂŠ103674 they've madeÂŠ103676 peaceÂŠ103676 with Yehoshua and \add âthe IsraelisÂŠ103683\add*.â
\v 5 \add âSoÂŠ103685\add* those fiveÂŠ103687 AmoriteÂŠ103690 kingsÂŠ103689 (from YerushalemÂŠ103692, HebronÂŠ103695, Yarmut, Lakish, and EglonÂŠ103704) joined together to go to GibeonÂŠ103712 and theirÂŠ103708 \add armiesÂŠ103708\add* campedÂŠ103709 there to fight againstÂŠ103714 itÂŠ103714.
\p
\v 6 The \add âleaders\add* of GibeonÂŠ103718 \add hurriedly\add* sentÂŠ103716 to Yehoshua in the campÂŠ103724 at GilgalÂŠ103725, saying, âDon'tÂŠ103727 \add âabandon\add* yourÂŠ103730 servantsÂŠ103731. Come quicklyÂŠ103734 and helpÂŠ103737 us, and saveÂŠ103735 us becauseÂŠ103738 all the kingsÂŠ103743 of the AmoritesÂŠ103744 who live in the hill countryÂŠ103746 have combined againstÂŠ103740 us.â
\v 7 \add âSoÂŠ103748\add* YehoshuaÂŠ103749 and his warriors and prize fightersÂŠ103757 \add âheaded off\add* from GilgalÂŠ103752,
\v 8 and YahwehÂŠ103765 told \add *him\add*, âDon'tÂŠ103768 be afraidÂŠ103771 of them, becauseÂŠ103773 \add âyou'll have the victory over them\add*ânone of them will be able to standÂŠ103778 against you.â
\p
\v 9 Yehoshua \add and his men\add* spent the nightÂŠ103789 moving in, and thenÂŠ103783 \add âsurprised the alliance\add*,
\v 10 and YahwehÂŠ103796 confusedÂŠ103795 them \add âas the Israelis approached\add* and \add caused them\add* to be badly defeatedÂŠ103799 atÂŠ103803 GibeonÂŠ103803. ThenÂŠ103795 \add #they\add* chased them onÂŠ103803 the road going to Beyt-HoronÂŠ103809 and killed them as far as AzekahÂŠ103813 and MakkedahÂŠ103816.
\v 11 As they fled from the Israelis on the slope down from Beyt-HoronÂŠ103827 heading towards AzekahÂŠ103838, YahwehÂŠ103828 hurled largeÂŠ103832 hailstones down on them from the sky andÂŠ103818 they diedâ\add actually\add* more of them died from the hail than were killedÂŠ103847 withÂŠ103819 swordsÂŠ103850 by the \add âIsraelis\add*.
\p
\v 12 Then Yehoshua spokeÂŠ103854 to YahwehÂŠ103859 onÂŠ103871 the dayÂŠ103857 that \add âhe gave them victory over the AmoritesÂŠ103862\add*, and \add âinÂŠ103871 frontÂŠ103863 of the IsraelisÂŠ103865\add* he saidÂŠ103866,
\q1 âSun, stay stillÂŠ103872 over GibeonÂŠ103871,
\q1 âand moonÂŠ103873, over the Ayyalon Valley.
\m
\v 13 ThenÂŠ103877 the sun stood still and the moonÂŠ103879 stood still untilÂŠ103881 the nationÂŠ103884 had avengedÂŠ103883 themselves of their enemiesÂŠ103885. (Isn't that writtenÂŠ103889 aboutÂŠ103902 in the Jashar scrollÂŠ103892? The sun stood still in the middleÂŠ103896 of the sky and it didn'tÂŠ103886 hurry to go around for almost a whole dayÂŠ103902.\x + \xo 10:13: \xt 2Sam 1:18.\x*
\v 14 ThereÂŠ103916 had never beforeÂŠ103909 been a dayÂŠ103907 like that, andÂŠ103905 nothing like it sinceÂŠ103910 thenÂŠ103905, when YahwehÂŠ103912 listenedÂŠ103911 to a man's voiceÂŠ103913, becauseÂŠ103915 \add *he\add* was fightingÂŠ103917 for YisraelÂŠ103918.)
\p
\v 15 Then Yehoshua and all YisraelÂŠ103925 returnedÂŠ103921 to their campÂŠ103929 at GilgalÂŠ103930.
