\v 9 MoshehÂŠ106102 \add âpromised me\add* that dayÂŠ106103, saying, âThe land \add âthat you walked onÂŠ106113\add* will certainly be for an inheritanceÂŠ106116 for you andÂŠ106101 your sons \add âforeverÂŠ106120\add*, becauseÂŠ106121 you were \add âcompletely loyal to\add* my godÂŠ106125 YahwehÂŠ106124.â\x + \xo 14:9: \xt Num 14:24.\x*
\v 10 Now, listen. Yahweh has kept me alive these forty-fiveÂŠ106136 years since Yahweh said that to MoshehÂŠ106148, \add back\add* when YisraelÂŠ106152 was walking inÂŠ106153 the wildernessÂŠ106153. \add âYes, believe itÂŠ106151 or not, I'm now eighty-fiveÂŠ106161.\add*
\v 11 I'm still as strongÂŠ106166 today as \add I was\add* on the day that MoshehÂŠ106171 sent me. \add âJust like I could fight back then, I can still fight or travel just the same\add*.
\v 12 \add âSo\add* now, please give me that hill countryÂŠ106186 that Yahweh \add âpromised\add* that day, becauseÂŠ106194 you yourself heardÂŠ106197 \add âme say\add* that the AnakimÂŠ106202 lived thereÂŠ106203 inÂŠ106198 fortifiedÂŠ106206 citiesÂŠ106204. \add So now,\add* perhapsÂŠ106207 Yahweh will help me to take them over just as \add *he\add* said.â
