\v 3 \add âButÂŠ107172\add* Zelofehad (son of HeferÂŠ107175, son of GileadÂŠ107178, son of MakirÂŠ107181, son of MenashshehÂŠ107184) had no sonsâonly daughters who were named MahlahÂŠ107197, NoahÂŠ107198, HoglahÂŠ107199, Milkah, andÂŠ107172 TirzahÂŠ107201.
\v 4 They approached the priestÂŠ107206 Eleazar and Yehoshua and the other leadersÂŠ107214 and said, âYahweh toldÂŠ107217 MoshehÂŠ107220 to give us an inheritance along with our brothers.â \add âSoÂŠ107203\add* he\f + \fr 17:4 \ft It's not clear who this âheâ refers to hereâsome translations choose Eleazar (implied by the sentence structure) and others choose Yehoshua (implied by past allocations of land).\f* gave them an inheritance (like he'd given theirÂŠ107236 uncles), as Yahweh \add âhad instructedÂŠ107217 them\add*.\x + \xo 17:4: \xt Num 27:1-7.\x*
\v 5 \add âSoÂŠ107238\add* tenÂŠ107242 blocks were allocated to MenashshehÂŠ107241 \add tribe\add* as well as GileadÂŠ107245 andÂŠ107238 BashanÂŠ107246 whichÂŠ107247 were across the YordanÂŠ107249
