\v 3 so that if \add âsomeone accidentallyÂŠ108661 kills someone else\add*, theyÂŠ108665 can escape thereÂŠ108656 andÂŠ108665 be safe \add âfrom the dead person'sÂŠ108660 family\add*.
\v 4 WhenÂŠ108671 \add @that person\add* flees to one of theseÂŠ108677 citiesÂŠ108676, \add they mustÂŠ108671\add* standÂŠ108678 atÂŠ108683 the city gate and tell the eldersÂŠ108684 there what happened. ThenÂŠ108671 they should bring \add @the person\add* into the city and give \add âthem a placeÂŠ108699 there to live inÂŠ108683\add*.
