\p
\v 1 Then Yehoshua \add âsummonedÂŠ109650\add* the tribesÂŠ109655 of Reuben and Gad, and the MenashshehÂŠ109656 half-tribe
\v 2 andÂŠ109671 told them, âYou yourselves have obeyedÂŠ109671 everything that Yahweh'sÂŠ109670 servantÂŠ109669 MoshehÂŠ109668 instructedÂŠ109666 you to do. In additionÂŠ109658, you've all followed everything that I told you.\x + \xo 22:2: \xt Num 32:20-32; Josh 1:12-15.\x*
\v 3 You've all \add ^supported\add* your \add âfellow tribes\add* all this timeÂŠ109686 and fulfilled what your godÂŠ109697 YahwehÂŠ109696 \add ârequested of youÂŠ109681 all\add*,
\v 4 andÂŠ109699 now \add *he\add* has enabled \add âthese other tribes\add* to rest \add from battle\add* just like he told them he would. \add âSoÂŠ109699\add* now, you all may goÂŠ109709 back to your homes thatÂŠ109716 Yahweh'sÂŠ109701 servantÂŠ109721 MoshehÂŠ109720 gaveÂŠ109718 you onÂŠ109723 the \add âother\add* sideÂŠ109723 of the river.
\v 5 Only do takeÂŠ109728 care to \add continue to\add* obey the instructions and the law thatÂŠ109737 Yahweh'sÂŠ109743 servantÂŠ109741 MoshehÂŠ109740 gave you: to loveÂŠ109744 your godÂŠ109748 Yahweh, to \add âfollow him and his instructions\add*, to \add âstay close to him\add*, and to serveÂŠ109758 him with all your heartsÂŠ109761 and your \add inner\add* selves.â
\v 6 ThenÂŠ109766 YehoshuaÂŠ109767 blessedÂŠ109766 them andÂŠ109766 sentÂŠ109768 them on their way to return to their \add âhomes\add*.
\v 7 (MoshehÂŠ109780 had given the BashanÂŠ109781 to the half of the MenashshehÂŠ109778 half-tribe, and Yehoshua had given \add land\add* onÂŠ109781 the \add âwestern\add* sideÂŠ109788 of the YordanÂŠ109791 to the otherÂŠ109788 half.) \add When\add* he'd blessedÂŠ109800 them
