\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 10 \add âThe warriors from the tribesÂŠ109888 of\add* Reuven, GadÂŠ109886, and the MenashshehÂŠ109889 half-tribe arrived at the YordanÂŠ109894 river (still on the CanaanÂŠ109879 side) and theyÂŠ109872 builtÂŠ109880 a very largeÂŠ109896 and noticeable altar thereÂŠ109890 \add before crossing over to go home\add*.
\v 11 \add WhenÂŠ109899\add* the \add other\add* \add âIsraelisÂŠ109902\add* heardÂŠ109899 \add about it\add*, theyÂŠ109905 said, âLook, the men \add âfrom the tribesÂŠ109913 of\add* Reuven, GadÂŠ109911, andÂŠ109899 the MenashshehÂŠ109914 half-tribe have builtÂŠ109905 the altarÂŠ109917 at the \add âentrance to this\add* CanaanÂŠ109922 regionÂŠ109921 down at the YordanÂŠ109926 on \add *our\add* sideÂŠ109929.â
\p
\v 12 \add âHearing that, those from the western side of the Yordan assembledÂŠ109936 at ShilohÂŠ109943 to goÂŠ109944 to battleÂŠ109946 with the two andÂŠ109936 a half tribes on the eastern side\add*.
\v 13 \add Meanwhile\add*, theyÂŠ109949 sentÂŠ109949 the priestÂŠ109979 Finehas (Eleazar'sÂŠ109978 son) \add across\add* into the GileadÂŠ109972 regionÂŠ109971 \add to talk\add* with \add the leaders from\add* the tribesÂŠ109966 of ReubenÂŠ109957, GadÂŠ109962, and the MenashshehÂŠ109968 half-tribe.
\v 14 \add @Finehas\add* took ten leaders with himâimportant leaders from each of the IsraeliÂŠ109991 tribesÂŠ109991 \add from the western side\add*.
\v 15 They \add crossed over\add* to the GileadÂŠ110022 regionÂŠ110021 to talk to \add the leaders from\add* the tribesÂŠ110016 of ReubenÂŠ110007, GadÂŠ110012, andÂŠ110002 the MenashshehÂŠ110018 half-tribe. They saidÂŠ110023,
